Definition.WordDefinition:
Unused \Un*used"\, a. 1. Not used; as, an unused book; an unused apartment. [1913 Webster]
2. Not habituated; unaccustomed. [1913 Webster]
Unused to bend, impatient of control. --Thomson. [1913 Webster]

unused adj 1: not yet used or soiled; "a fresh shirt"; "a fresh sheet of paper"; "an unused envelope" [syn: {fresh}] 2: not yet put into use; "we boughtt an unused car for a change" 3: not in active use; "the machinery sat idle during the strike"; "idle hands" [syn: {idle}]
